Campus Ambassador

Ready to lead your campus into the future of tech? Become a Campus Ambassador for Hack-Nirvana and unlock exciting opportunities ahead!

Hackathon Ambassador Guidelines

Please read the following guidelines carefully. By agreeing to participate, you acknowledge and consent to these terms:

  • As a campus ambassador, you are responsible for promoting the hackathon event through various channels (social media, word of mouth, posters, etc.).
  • You are expected to engage with fellow students, create excitement, and encourage registrations.
  • You must maintain professional and respectful conduct while representing the hackathon.
  • You will have specific tasks and deadlines to meet, and we expect timely completion of tasks.
  • Any misuse of the program or failure to adhere to guidelines may result in disqualification.

Exclusive Ambassador Perks

  • Certificate of Volunteering: Receive an official certificate upon successful completion of the program.
  • Networking Opportunities: Connect with fellow ambassadors, mentors, and industry professionals, expanding your network in the tech and innovation space.
  • Leadership Experience: Gain valuable leadership and marketing experience, enhancing your resume and helping you develop skills for future professional growth.
  • Special Recognition: Stand out as a top ambassador in the hackathon community and gain recognition on the official website and social media platforms.
  • Placement and Higher Education Assistance: Get special access to career development opportunities, including placement assistance and support for pursuing higher education opportunities.

Coordinator-Level Responsibilities

As a Campus Ambassador, you will take on responsibilities similar to that of a Coordinator, helping to organize, promote, and lead initiatives within your college or university. This involves:

  • Promoting the hackathon event to your peers.
  • Recruiting participants and encouraging sign-ups.
  • Leading engagement efforts on campus.
  • Being the point of contact for event-related information.
  • Collaborating with the hackathon organizing team to ensure smooth communication and event success.

This role offers an opportunity to showcase your organizational, leadership, and teamwork skills.
